Attention is constantly called to peculiar Lucianic con· structions and words, and to other later usages. Historical‚ archaeological, philosophical, and mythological questions are succinctly discussed‚ with references to the original authorities or to modern treatises.

His modern tone, his felicitous style, his strong common sense, and his abounding humor make Lucian delightful reading3 and it is hoped that this edition may help to make his writings more widely used in our colleges than has hitherto been the case.
